Who'd have thought that 2 ingredients could make such a delicious dessert? I made a fruit salad with lots of diced fruit tossed with a gingered simple syrup, and put a scoop of this sorbet in the middle. It was a delicious, light end to a heavy meal.

Rating: 4
Simple and delicious! I used Florida Honey Tangerines and they were so sweet on their own I almost decided against any sugar. I ended up using 1/4 cup of Splenda. Next time I will eliminiate altogether if tangerines are extra sweet. Try this one - you'll be pleased.

