Delicious, but too sweet for me. Next time, I'll try only 1/2 cup of sugar. (If you don't have superfine sugar, just put the sugar through a blender or food processor for a little while).

Rating: 4
This recipe is healthier and tastier than any other tangerine sorbet recipe I have seen. I needed to use about 18 large tangerines to get this amount of juice. The sorbet is simply wonderful and is already my favorite cold dessert. I will make this in the future, not only for my husband, but for guests and other friends.

Rating: 4
So refreshing and delicoius, especially after a heavy meal! I serve the sorbet in the hollowed out tangerine rinds for a simple and beautiful presentation. Passing the scooped out tangerine through a food mill easily extracts the juice.

